# GitHub Copilot Instructions

## Project: {{PROJECT_NAME}}

This is an **ExpressionEngine 7.x** CMS website using native EE templates with Tailwind CSS and Alpine.js.

## Tech Stack

- **CMS**: ExpressionEngine 7.x (PHP-based)
- **CSS**: Tailwind CSS via PostCSS
- **JavaScript**: Alpine.js for interactivity
- **Environment**: DDEV local development
- **Database**: {{DDEV_DB_TYPE}} {{DDEV_DB_VERSION}}
- **PHP**: {{DDEV_PHP}}+

## Coding Standards

### PHP
- Follow PSR-12 coding standards with 4-space indentation
- Use type hints for parameters and return types
- Use early returns to reduce nesting

### HTML/Templates
- Use 2-space indentation
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- EE templates use `.html` extension
- Prefix partials with underscore: `_header`

### CSS
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes over custom CSS
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use BEM naming for custom CSS classes

### JavaScript
- Use ES6+ features with 2-space indentation
- Prefer Alpine.js `x-data` components

## Key Patterns

### ExpressionEngine Channel Entries
```html
{exp:channel:entries channel="pages" limit="10" dynamic="no" disable="categories|member_data"}
    <article>{title}</article>
{/exp:channel:entries}
```

### Stash Caching
```html
{exp:stash:set name="content" save="yes" scope="site"}
    {!-- expensive query here --}
{/exp:stash:set}
{exp:stash:get name="content"}
```

### Alpine.js Components
```html
<div x-data="{ open: false }">
    <button @click="open = !open">Toggle</button>
    <div x-show="open">Content</div>
</div>
```

## Security Requirements

- Never commit `.env.php` or credentials
- Use parameterized queries for custom SQL
- Sanitize all user input before output
- Include CSRF tokens via `{csrf_token}` in forms

